Indeed, when he was just 11 years old, Albert wrote in a school essay,

00:01:31.242 --> 00:01:35.062
“When I leave school, I should like to be the Official Executioner.”

00:01:36.372 --> 00:01:42.162
His father was an executioner, his uncle was an executioner, and sure enough young

00:01:42.212 --> 00:01:46.955
Albert Pierrepoint would go on to achieve his dream, becoming the country’s most

00:01:46.965 --> 00:01:53.365
famous executioner, and being responsible for the executions of up to 600 people.

00:01:54.465 --> 00:02:02.965
When Henry Pierrepoint died in 1922, his 17-year-old son, Albert, received two blue diaries.

00:02:03.755 --> 00:02:08.005
Were they his memoirs, his reflections on life, love

00:02:08.005 --> 00:02:11.185
letters to his wife, or a great unpublished novel?

